<P>AN ORATION, DELIVERED <HI>JULY</HI> 4<HI>th, A. D.</HI> 1796, IN THE BAPTIST MEETING-HOUSE, IN NEWPORT; IN COMMEMORATION OF THE TWENTIETH ANNIVERSARY OF AMERICAN INDEPENDENCE.</P>
<P>BY <HI>ABRAHAM REDWOOD ELLERY.</HI></P>
<LG>
<L>"Westward the course of Empire takes its way;</L>
<L>"The four first Acts already past;</L>
<L>"The fifth will close the Drama with the day,</L>
<L>"Time's noblest Offspring is the last."</L>
</LG>
<P>WARREN (RHODE-ISLAND): PRINTEED BY NATHANIEL PHILLIPS, M,DCC,XVI.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="invitation">
