<OPENER><DATELINE><HI>NEWPORT,</HI><DATE><HI>MAY</HI> 21, 1796.</DATE></DATELINE></OPENER>
<P><HI>THE undersigned Citizens of Newport present the compliments to</HI> Abraham Redwood Ellery, <ABBR><HI>Esq.</HI></ABBR> <HI>and being im|pressed with a sense of the propriety of an</HI> annual recognition <HI>of the irresistible feelings, sentiments and principles, that animated</HI> United America, <HI>in the year</HI> 1776, <HI>to declare herself</HI> independ|ent, <HI>request the favor of him to deliver, in the Baptist Meeting|House in this Town, on the</HI> fourth <HI>of July next, an Oration in cel|ebration of that ever-memorable event.</HI></P>
